volume in Consumer Banking.
●Investment and brokera ge services income decreased  $258
million  primarily due to lower transactional revenue and a
decrease in assets under management (AUM) pricing,
partially offset by the positive impact of AUM flows and higher
market valuations.
●Investment banking fees increased  $315 million  due to
