On Decemb er 22, 2017, the President signed into law the Tax
Act which made significant changes to federal income tax law
including, among other things, reducing the statutory corporate
income tax rate to 21 percent from 35 percent  and changing the
taxation of the Corporation’ s non-U.S. busines s activities. The
impact on net income in 2017  was $2.9 billion , driven by $2.3
billion  in income tax expense , largely from a lower valuation of
certain U.S. deferred tax assets and liabilities. The change in the
statutory tax rate also impacted the Corporation’ s tax-
advantaged energy investments, resulting in a downward
valuation adjustment of $946 million  recorded in other income
and a related income tax benefit of $347 million, which when
netted against the $2.3 billion , resulted in a net impact on income
tax expense of $1.9 billion .
